summary:
I am a dynamic professional who enjoys challenges, with a strong skillset and relevant experience in the commercial sector.

I appreciated my first professional challenge: successfully integrating a trade delegation in Paris into a Spanish multinational company.
The excellent results I achieved in this first experience enabled me to take on a second challenge at the head office in Spain.

I worked to build relationships, serving as a liaison between different cultural contacts and facilitating communication between the different languages. I also reached sales targets and ensured customer satisfaction and loyalty through my work.

My next professional achievement was assembling and managing a sales team in charge of cross-border commerce between France and Spain within a leading company in the wine and liquor market.
Once again, I utilised my coordination and listening skills to facilitate communication between the different languages and cultures in order to reach sales targets.

Upon relocating to the Netherlands, I opted to dedicate my time to my family in this newest step and adapt to a new culture. In addition, this period enabled me to complete different courses in subjects including Dutch language, painting and cooking.

I went back to active working life almost a year ago and I am looking for new and interesting challenges to achieve my personal and professional growth.
